The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Fine Print

 Woody Cruz

 Dream Role

 Madrid, Feb. 2 (Reuters): Oscar-nominated Spanish actress Penelope Cruz is to star in the new Woody Allen film, to be shot this summer in Barcelona, newspaper El Pais reported today.

 Quoting Cruzs agent, El Pais said the film was still without a title but that the sought-after actress would speak in Spanish and in English.

 has shot two of his last features in London Match Point and Scoop and announced some time ago that he would film in Barcelona.

 His latest film, Cassandras Dream, starring Ewan McGregor and Colin Farrell, has yet to be released. Cruz is currently nominated for an Oscar for best actress for her leading role in Spanish director Pedro Almodovars Volver.




